  "text": "For the diagnosis of cirrhosis in CHC patients, we obtained an AUC of 0.830. This AUC was also very close to the pooled AUC of 0.82 (95%CI 0.79-0.86) reported in Shaheen's meta-analysis. At thresholds of 1.0 and 2.0, estimated sensitivities were 76% (95%CI 68-82%) and 49% (43-55%), and specificities 71% (69-73%) and 91% (90-93%), respectively. [CITATION_1] Our sensitivities at the same thresholds were 77 and 38%, and specificities 77 and 92%. The 95%CIs of all these parameters overlapped those estimated in the meta-analysis. In our series, the cutoff point showing the best sensitivity (89.4%) and specificity (70.9%) was an APRI value of 0.7532, which is close to the 1.0 threshold of the meta-analysis, and almost identical to the one originally found by Wai.",
